October 2 marks the birth anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi. Since 2007, this day is also celebrated as the International Day of Non-Violence.On Monday evening, the India High Commission hosted a commemoration event at the University of Nairobi where Kenya School of Law director PLO Lumumba gave the keynote address.Present were Ethiopia high commissioner Dina Mufti, his Rwanda counterpart James Kimonyo as well as Indian High Commissioner Suchitra Durai and industrialist Dr Manu Chandaria.